content:
The Multi Auto rating procedure uses the auto_MultiInstanceRating Integration Procedure to calculate coverage prices for the Multi Auto product. This procedure is called by the quote business process when a broker or customer service rep generates a quote.

Here's how it works:

* The Multi Auto product includes a Vehicle insured item spec as the primary multi-instance item that auto policies will insure.
* You can create quotes for multiple vehicles.
* The rating procedure uses input data passed into it to calculate prices based on risk-based calculations.
* On the product model, pricing formulas are used to roll up the prices. The formula total policy premium is calculated by summing up premiums for various coverage types (e.g., BIPD, COLL, CCD, MED, UM, Rental).
* After understanding the rating procedure, you can simulate it on the Multi Auto product model and see how it affects quote flows.

Rating Input

The Multi Auto product uses a Vehicle insured item spec as the primary multi-instance item that auto policies will insure. You can create quotes for multiple vehicles.

Rating Procedure

A rating is a risk-based calculation of a premium based on a set of input characteristics. The procedure returns coverage prices, which are then rolled up by Vlocity using product model pricing formulas.

Pricing Formulas

On the Simulate tab of the product model, you'll see the Rating Inputs and Rating Outputs mapped from the rating procedure. The formula to calculate the per-vehicle premium is:

premiumBIPD + premiumCOLL + premiumCCD + premiumMED + premiumUM+premiumRental

The total policy premium for this product is calculated by summing up these premiums.

Next Steps

* Simulate the rating procedure on the Multi Auto product model.
* Go to the quote flows to see how the Auto Application rates products for quotes.
title: Multi Auto Insurance Rating Procedure
